{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17636184","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17636184"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T18:24:42+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T18:24:42+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17570"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17570","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17570"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.1,0.24,0.52,0.05,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10260"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77693"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10260"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17570"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63206"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10086"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23973"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23982"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77693","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77693"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EBasal metabolic rate (BMR) represents the energy expenditure required to maintain basic life processes in a resting, fasting state.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes basal metabolic rate as a percentage of total daily energy expenditure in a sedentary individual?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["20-30%","40-50%","60-75%","80-90%","95-100%"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn sedentary individuals, \u003Cstrong\u003E60-75%\u003C/strong\u003E of total daily energy expenditure is attributed to basal metabolic rate. This represents the energy needed to maintain basic life processes at rest.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E20-30%\u003C/strong\u003E - This is too low and represents the contribution of physical activity to total daily energy expenditure\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E40-50%\u003C/strong\u003E - This underestimates BMR\u0027s contribution in sedentary individuals\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E80-90%\u003C/strong\u003E - This overestimates BMR\u0027s contribution, not accounting for other energy expenditure components\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E95-100%\u003C/strong\u003E - This would incorrectly suggest almost no energy is used for physical activity or digestion\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe remaining energy expenditure comes from physical activity (15-30%) and the thermic effect of food (10%). These proportions can vary significantly based on activity level, with BMR representing a smaller percentage in very active individuals.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Basal metabolic rate represents the minimum energy required to maintain vital body functions at complete rest.","Total daily energy expenditure includes basal metabolic rate, physical activity, and thermic effect of food.","Basal metabolic rate accounts for 60-75% of total daily energy expenditure in sedentary individuals."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63206"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"que